# Site URL used for canonical metadata and previews
SITE=https://steveroberts.me

# NOTE: Why are analytics IDs and other public build-time values not here?
#
# This is a fully static Astro site. All values must be baked in during `astro build`;
# there is no server runtime to supply them afterwards.
#
# Cloudflare "Variables and Secrets" are runtime bindings for the Worker's fetch handler
# — they are NOT available as process.env or import.meta.env during the build step, and
# cannot be used to supply build-time values for static sites.
#
# Public, non-secret values that are needed at build time (e.g. GA Measurement ID) are
# stored directly in src/config.ts where they are always available and version-controlled.
#
# Genuine secrets for the contact form Pages Function (functions/api/contact.ts) should
# be set in the Cloudflare Pages project's secret store, not here:
#   TURNSTILE_SECRET_KEY
#   AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID
#   AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY
#   AWS_REGION
#   SES_FROM_EMAIL
#   SES_TO_EMAIL
